-- Rostowski Sees `Significant, Not Radical' Polish Pension Changes Next Year
-- B y   D a v i d   M c Q u a i d
-- 2010-11-30T06:59:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-30/rostowski-sees-significant-not-radical-polish-pension-changes-next-year.html
Poland will make “significant, not
radical” changes in its pension system next year by choosing
from seven options, including cutting transfers to private
pension funds and introducing non-tradeable pension bonds,
Finance Minister Jacek Rostowski said today in an interview on
Tok FM Radio.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David McQuaid at 
